<HL>
   Latin American Fund Files
   For Initial Public Offering
</HL>
<DATE>
05/22/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C14
</SO>
<IN>
MUTUAL AND MONEY-MARKET FUNDS (FND)
INITIAL STOCK OFFERINGS (INI)
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- An investment group filed with the Securities
and Exchange Commission for the initial public offering of a
closed-end fund that will invest primarily in Mexico, Chile
and Brazil.
   The offering is for a minimum of four million shares, or
$60 million. A syndicate led by Salomon Inc. will underwrite
the offering. The fund, called the Latin American Investment
Fund Inc., will be jointly managed by Salomon Brothers Asset
Management Inc. and BEA Associates Inc.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The fund will invest primarily in stocks listed on major
Latin American exchanges, but its managers will also be able
to invest in Latin American debt for trading or conversion
into equity investments.
</TEXT>
